'''Don Deedson Louicius''' (born 11 February 2001), commonly known as '''Louicius Deedson''', is a Haitian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right winger]] for [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] club [[FC Dallas]] and the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==International career==
He made his debut for [[Haiti national football team]] on 25 March 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF first round|World Cup qualifier]] against Belize.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FIFA]]|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/nccamerica/matches/match/400136266/#match-lineups|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108103525/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/nccamerica/matches/match/400136266/#match-lineups|url-status=dead|archive-date=8 January 2021|title=Haiti v Belize game report|date=25 March 2021}}</ref> He scored his first two goals for Haiti against Jamaica in a CONCACAF Nations League match against Jamaica.<ref name=":0" />

